snippet.textDisplay: No. The closer together your hands are, the more you activate the lower lats. The wider your hands are, the more you activate your upper lats. It really depends on what you are trying to achieve. Regardless of how wide or close you do pull ups, you will ALWAYS activate the brachialis muscle, because it is a much smaller muscle and will activate and fatigue first. Leg position makes absolutely no difference, unless you are doing a pull up in an L-Sit and working your core at the same time.  Tightness is BAD. You need to stay loose and flexible at all times.  Elbow position is dependent on how wide you are doing your pull ups, which again has everything to do with what part of the Lats you are trying to activate. This is silly.

snippet.textDisplay: What a lot of people don’t realize is that weighted pull ups are the best exercise to get the v taper. Deadlifts may help but it’ll thicken the shit out of your waist and love handles, bent over rows don’t have anywhere near the lat activation as shown by study after study. The body is literally made to use this movement biomechanically and from evolution to pull itself up and pull things towards it with this movement. The better you are at doing that the more aesthetically pleasing your physique.
